headline: Software Stocks Feel the Blues, But Some Look Set To Rebound
summary: A notable exception has been  Palantir  among a select few helping to prop up the  iShares Expanded Tech-Software Sector ETF  IGV.  One is  Circle internet Group  the financial software player, which appears poised for a deeper pullback.  My downside target sits at $135, which would fill the gap from June 13 and mark a retest of the bull flag breakout from June 16, a sensible technical level for buyers to reassess positioning.
